  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Numerous surgical techniques have been developped for the treatment of chondral and
      osteochondral defects of the knee. Among those techniques autologous chondrocyte
      transplantation (ACT) was promising but have potential drawbacks. A novel development by TBF
      is available. The aim of this randomized trial is to compared this new ACT technique to
      mosaicoplasty. Final outcomes were measured at 2 years using clinical evaluation scoring
      system (International Knee Documentation Committee), MRI and arthroscopy with biopsy. 64
      patients are needed to detect a mean IKDC difference of at least 15 points with 90% power at
      a 5% alpha level. Twelve surgical centers in France are involved.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
