  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  isolated femoral osteochondral lesion

          -  aged 18 to 50

          -  grade 3 or 4 lesion (ICRS) sized 2,5 cm2 to 7,5 cm2.

          -  IKDC score below 55

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  pregnancy

          -  allergy

          -  arthrosis

          -  varus or valgus angle greater than 10°

          -  ACL laxity

          -  Severe chronic disease

          -  BMI &gt; 30 Kg/m2

          -  HIV, B or C Hepatitis
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
